    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nTUI: server --listen error is only briefly visible\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\n2. Run `:echo serverlist()` in Nvim\n3. Run another `nvim --clean --listen` followed by the previous Nvim's server address\n4. The `Failed to --listen: address already in use` error is only briefly visible\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe `Failed to --listen: address already in use` error is visible until the user clears the screen.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-525+g52c61d9690\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
