        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Unless `:detach` also sends a UI event...?\n\nWould like `:detach` to work with all UIs, even if the UI doesn't explicitly support it. I guess sending a UI event could just be an extra (optional) \"hint\".\n\nIdeally we can avoid a UI event, and instead [set a flag on the channel](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/21608#issuecomment-2955707949), ~~or send a command (via the channel) to the UI client from the server, or the client checks server state via the channel.~~ (Edit: the last 2 are equivalent to a UI event, so nevermind)",
