        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> I think we discussed long ago adding a `exit` UI event, this has been requested by GUIs before.\n\nSomewhat off-topic, and not a blocker: this reminds me of a repeating thought, which is that \"editor events\" and \"UI events\" are unnecessarily bifurcated. Editor events like `VimLeave` should also go to the \"UI channel\". This could be opt-in via `nvim_ui_attach()`. But it's silly that we are duplicating the same kind of events in 2 different places. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34399",
